#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.236"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.236:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.236:0.2"
msgid "24. Kammavagga"
msgstr "24. Deeds"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.236:0.3"
msgid "236. Dutiyasikkhāpadasutta"
msgstr "236. Training Rules (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.236:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā paveditāni."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with "
"my own insight."

msgctxt "an4.236:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. </p><ol><li>
msgctxt "an4.236:1.3"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ;"
msgstr "There are dark deeds with dark results;"

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.236:1.4"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ;"
msgstr "bright deeds with bright results;"

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.236:1.5"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ;"
msgstr "dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results; and"

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.236:1.6"
msgid ""
"atthi, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright results, which "
"lead to the ending of deeds."

#. </li></ol><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.235"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.236:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ?"
msgstr "And what are dark deeds with dark results?"

#. VAR: ekaccena mātā → ekacco mātā (pts1) | ekacco mātaraṃ (mr)
#. VAR: pitā → pitaraṃ (mr)
#. VAR: voropito → voropitā (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: arahaṃ → arahantaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: voropito → voropitā (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: uppāditaṃ → uppāditā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.236:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekaccena mātā jīvitā voropitā hoti, pitā jīvitā voropito "
"hoti, arahaṃ jīvitā voropito hoti, tathāgatassa duṭṭhena cittena lohitaṃ "
"uppāditaṃ hoti, saṃgho bhinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"It's when someone murders their mother or father or a perfected one. They "
"maliciously shed the blood of a Realized One. Or they cause a schism in the "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an4.236:2.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ."
msgstr "These are called dark deeds with dark results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.236:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?"
msgstr "And what are bright deeds with bright results?"

#. VAR: sammādiṭṭhi → sammādiṭṭhiko (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.236:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato "
"hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya "
"vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā "
"paṭivirato hoti, anabhijjhālu hoti, abyāpannacitto hoti, sammādiṭṭhi hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or commit sexual "
"misconduct. They don’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or "
"nonsensical. And they’re content, kind-hearted, with right view."

msgctxt "an4.236:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ."
msgstr "These are called bright deeds with bright results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.236:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?"
msgstr "And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?"

msgctxt "an4.236:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ "
"abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ "
"kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, "
"speech, and mind. These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and "
"bright results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.236:5.1"
msgid ""
"Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya "
"saṃvattati?"
msgstr ""
"And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright "
"results, which lead to the ending of deeds?"

msgctxt "an4.236:5.2"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yamidaṃ kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ … pe … idaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"It’s the intention to give up dark deeds with dark results, bright deeds "
"with bright results, and both dark and bright deeds with both dark and "
"bright results. These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither "
"dark nor bright results, which lead to the ending of deeds."

msgctxt "an4.236:5.3"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"paveditānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with "
"my own insight.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.236:5.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
